Shared responsibility
----
https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/security/fundamentals/shared-responsibility

High Availability: remain operational even during palnned and unplanned outages
High Uptime. 99.99%
Scalability: Ability to add/remove resources
 - to adopt to changing usage patterns
 - to handle high amount of traffic with out changing the system design/ code
 - verticle scallaing has an upper limit such as 96 vCPU, 384 GN memory. doesnt answer/fix the availability
 - horizontal scalling - scalling in , out - adding more servers and resources, no limits to the scalling : complexity - load balancers
Elasticity: ability to quickly scale up and down resources


 
